2026-05-17 16:33:45 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #4 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"code": "import pandas as pd\n\n# Load CSV from provided s3 uri directly\ns3_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-archeology-easy-10/files/worldcities.csv'\n\n# Read CSV\ndf = pd.read_csv(s3_uri)\nprint('rows,cols', df.shape)\nprint('capital value counts:')\nprint(df['capital'].value_counts(dropna=False))\n\n# Filter to primary capitals\ncap_df = df[df['capital'] == 'primary'].copy()\nprint('primary rows:', len(cap_df))\n\n# For each country, pick the capital with largest population\n# population may have NaN; convert to numeric\ncap_df['population'] = pd.to_numeric(cap_df['population'], errors='coerce')\n# sort and drop duplicates keeping max population per country\ncap_df_sorted = cap_df.sort_values(['country','population'], ascending=[True, False])\ncap_one = cap_df_sorted.drop_duplicates(subset=['country'], keep='first')\nprint('unique countries with primary capital selected:', len(cap_one))\n\n# Compute average latitude\ncap_one['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(cap_one['lat'], errors='coerce')\navg_lat = cap_one['lat'].mean()\nprint('avg_lat_raw', avg_lat)\n\n# Round to 4 decimals\nprint('avg_lat_4', round(avg_lat,4))\n\n# Print final value for tool parsing\nprint(round(avg_lat,4))", "intent": "Compute average latitude of primary capitals, selecting the most populous capital per country when multiple are present, and round to 4 decimals.", "dataset_id": "kramabench-archeology-easy-10", "file_path": "files/worldcities.csv"}) [toolUseId=call_7uWftlmsUtYhzyic8sdIUVgS]
2026-05-17 16:33:45 | INFO | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Executing: execute_ideal({"code": "import pandas as pd\n\n# Load CSV from provided s3 uri directly\ns3_uri = 's3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-archeology-easy-10/files/worldcities.csv'\n\n# Read CSV\ndf = pd.read_csv(s3_uri)\nprint('rows,cols', df.shape)\nprint('capital value counts:')\nprint(df['capital'].value_counts(dropna=False))\n\n# Filter to primary capitals\ncap_df = df[df['capital'] == 'primary'].copy()\nprint('primary rows:', len(cap_df))\n\n# For each country, pick the capital with largest population\n# population may have NaN; convert to numeric\ncap_df['population'] = pd.to_numeric(cap_df['population'], errors='coerce')\n# sort and drop duplicates keeping max population per country\ncap_df_sorted = cap_df.sort_values(['country','population'], ascending=[True, False])\ncap_one = cap_df_sorted.drop_duplicates(subset=['country'], keep='first')\nprint('unique countries with primary capital selected:', len(cap_one))\n\n# Compute average latitude\ncap_one['lat'] = pd.to_numeric(cap_one['lat'], errors='coerce')\navg_lat = cap_one['lat'].mean()\nprint('avg_lat_raw', avg_lat)\n\n# Round to 4 decimals\nprint('avg_lat_4', round(avg_lat,4))\n\n# Print final value for tool parsing\nprint(round(avg_lat,4))", "intent": "Compute average latitude of primary capitals, selecting the most populous capital per country when multiple are present, and round to 4 decimals.", "dataset_id": "kramabench-archeology-easy-10", "file_path": "files/worldcities.csv"})
